\chapter{Public Exposure}

The local HTTP server is enough for a lecture room on the same LAN, but it
breaks down as soon as students sit on a different network.  We therefore keep
the network-facing exposure logic in its own module: the CLI can choose an
exposure strategy without learning any UPnP or SSH details.

